  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Respite for 40 Teens Affected by a Family Illness</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Two tailored respite holidays for 20 young people in Herefordshire and Gloucestershire, who are struggling to cope because a close family member has been diagnosed with a life-threatening illness.  At such a crucial age (11+), mental health provision is vital but shamefully inadequate.  Fostering peer support, teaching new skills and providing a safe space to deal with their emotions, Hope&apos;s residential breaks provide much-needed stability, rest and time away from a traumatic situation at home.</narrative>
  </description>
